<div class="content">
			

<!--Start Main Content-->


PLEASE NOTE:<P>
<UL>
<LI>If you have complaints about our agency, use our <a href="commission/complaint.html">on-line complaint form</a>.</li><BR>

<LI>If you have<b> complaints about your utility company or problems with your utility bill</b>, contact the <a href="http://www.cpuc.ca.gov/static/forms/complaint.htm">California Public Utilities Commission's Consumer Services Division.</a>  Customers
of SMUD or LADWP or other municipal utilities will need to call their local utility company's directors or ombudsman as the CPUC does not handle those complaints.
</UL>
<BR>




<p><span class="heading">To Contact Us By Phone or FAX</span></p>
<div class="toc">

<P><img src="cecimages/newbullet.gif" alt="bullet"><B>General Commission Information: 916-654-4287</B></P>

<P><img src="cecimages/newbullet.gif" alt="bullet"><B><a href="commission/phone_list.html">Commission main phone numbers and e-mail addresses</a></B></P>


<P><img src="cecimages/newbullet.gif" alt="bullet"><B>Renewable Energy & Consumer Energy Efficiency Information:</b>
<div class="toc">
Toll Free in California - 1-800-555-7794<BR>
Outside California - 916-654-4058
</div>
</p>


<P><b><img src="cecimages/newbullet.gif" alt="bullet">Title 24 Building & Appliance Efficiency Standards Hotline:</b>
<div class="toc">
Toll Free in California - 1-800-772-3300<BR>
Outside California - 916-654-5106
</div>
</p>


<P>Members of the News Media should contact Media & Public Communications Office: 916-654-4989</P>

</div>
<BR>


